Samsung Kenya last week donated Sh3.5 million Smartphones to the Ministry of Health in support of the fight against the coronavirus pandemic. In attendance were Mobile Samsung Electronics East Africa director Charles Kimari, Safaricom Foundation chief special officer and chairman Joseph Ogutu, and the National and Emergency Response Team, led by Health CAS Rashid Aman. Kimari said they saw the urge to donate the phones to improve communication among health workers and other frontline workers fighting the coronavirus.